faceoff_positive.comments:
This mascara is seriously cute. When I opened the box, I wasn't expecting the wand to have this clear crystal looking orb on top. It was such a nice surprise. I've never seen a mascara look like that before. Usually they're just plain tubes. This one feels way more high end than anything else I've used. 

Application was super smooth. I really liked the curved wand because it made it easy to get every lash. One thing I noticed though, it dries kinda fast. So if you're layering, you'll want to get it all on in one go. Once it sets, it's a little tough to add more. If I needed to fix something, I just dabbed my lashes with a makeup wipe to get them slightly wet again and that helped a lot.

I got around 24 hours of wear before I needed to reapply. I sleep with a mask on so that probably took some off. If you don't wear one, you might be able to stretch it to the full 36 hours like it says.

The best part for me is that it's plant based. I didn't have to stress about putting it near my eyes. No irritation, no burning, no watering, nothing. My eyes felt completely fine the whole time.

It also gave my lashes a nice lift and helped smooth out the ones that usually point in weird directions. My eyes looked more dramatic and put together but not over the top. I'd wear this to work, school, or just as an everyday go to.

This was my first MAC product and I'm impressed. You can tell they really care about the details from the packaging to what's inside. I'll definitely be checking out more from them. I received this product for free from Topbox Marketing for testing and review purposes.
faceoff_positive.headline: So Cute, Plant Based, I'm obsessed

faceoff_negative.comments: MAC Cosmetics' new MACStack Elevated Mascara features a uniquely curved brush and promises up to 165% instant lash lift with 36-hour wearâ€”regardless of your lash type. Sadly, it fell completely flat for me. The only thing that impressed me was the packaging. The wand handle is topped with a stunning crystal ball that gives the product a luxe, eye-catching, and innovative look. I expect mascara to give my eyelashes bold, dramatic length and definition in the deepest black shade possible without requiring me to apply multiple coats. Otherwise, there is no point in using mascara. The MACStack Elevated Mascara formula had the worst pigmentation ever. Even after applying multiple coats and experimenting with different angles, I saw little to no difference in my lashes. I received this product for free from Topbox Marketing for testing and review purposes.
faceoff_negative.headline: Super disappointed!
